            <li>Upgrade recommendations</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3>Professional Installation</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>200 amp main panel installation</li>
            <li>New circuit breakers</li>
            <li>Grounding system upgrade</li>
            <li>Service entrance connection</li>
            <li>Meter base upgrade (if needed)</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3>Permits & Inspections</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>City of Omaha permits pulled</li>
            <li>Coordination with OPPD</li>
            <li>Final inspection scheduling</li>
            <li>Code compliance certification</li>
            <li>Warranty documentation</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="problems-solved">
      <h2>Common Electrical Panel Problems We Solve</h2>
      <div class="problem-grid">
        <div class="problem-item">
          <h3>üî• Overloaded Circuits</h3>
          <p>Frequent breaker trips, flickering lights, and burning smells indicate your panel can't handle your home's electrical demand.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="problem-item">
          <h3>‚ö° Old Fuse Boxes</h3>
          <p>Replacing outdated fuse boxes with modern circuit breaker panels improves safety and increases home value.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="problem-item">
          <h3>üè† Home Additions</h3>
          <p>Adding square footage, pools, hot tubs, or EV chargers often requires panel capacity upgrades.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="problem-item">
          <h3>üîß Federal Pacific Panels</h3>
          <p>These recalled panels pose fire risks and should be replaced immediately for safety.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="problem-item">
          <h3>üí° Insufficient Amperage</h3>
          <p>Upgrading from 100 amp to 200 amp service accommodates modern electrical needs and appliances.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="problem-item">
          <h3>üè° Insurance Requirements</h3>
          <p>Many insurance companies require panel upgrades for homes with outdated electrical systems.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="our-process">
      <h2>Our Panel Upgrade Process</h2>
      <div class="process-steps">
        <div class="step">
          <div class="step-number">1</div>
          <div class="step-content">
            <h3>Free Consultation & Estimate</h3>
            <p>We inspect your current panel, assess your electrical needs, and provide a detailed estimate with no hidden fees.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="step">
          <div class="step-number">2</div>
          <div class="step-content">
            <h3>Permits & Utility Coordination</h3>
            <p>We handle all permit applications and coordinate with OPPD for temporary power disconnection during installation.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="step">
          <div class="step-number">3</div>
          <div class="step-content">
            <h3>Professional Installation</h3>
            <p>Our licensed electricians install your new 200 amp panel, upgrade grounding, and ensure all connections meet code.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="step">
          <div class="step-number">4</div>
          <div class="step-content">
            <h3>Testing & Inspection</h3>
            <p>We test all circuits, schedule city inspection, and provide you with all documentation and warranty information.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="why-choose-us">
      <h2>Why Choose Omaha Electrician for Panel Upgrades</h2>
      <div class="grid">
        <div class="benefit">
          <h3>‚úÖ Licensed & Insured</h3>
          <p>Nebraska state licensed electricians with full liability insurance and bonding for your protection.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="benefit">
          <h3>‚ö° Same-Day Service</h3>
          <p>Most panel upgrades completed in one day with minimal disruption to your daily routine.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="benefit">
          <h3>üí∞ Transparent Pricing</h3>
          <p>Upfront pricing with no hidden fees. We provide detailed estimates before any work begins.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="benefit">
          <h3>üõ°Ô∏è 5-Year Warranty</h3>
          <p>All panel upgrades include a comprehensive 5-year warranty on parts and labor.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="benefit">
          <h3>üìã Permit Handling</h3>
          <p>We pull all necessary permits and coordinate inspections so you don't have to worry about compliance.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="benefit">
          <h3>üîß Quality Materials</h3>
          <p>We use only top-tier panels from Square D, Cutler-Hammer, and other trusted manufacturers.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="emergency-service">
      <div class="emergency-card">
        <h2>üö® Emergency Panel Service Available 24/7</h2>
        <p>Electrical panel emergencies can't wait. If you're experiencing sparking, burning smells, or repeated power outages, call us immediately for emergency service throughout Omaha and surrounding areas.</p>
        <a href="tel:+1-402-555-1234" class="btn-emergency">Emergency Service: (402) 555-1234</a>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="service-area">
      <h2>Panel Upgrade Service Areas</h2>
      <div class="service-areas">
        <div class="area-column">
          <h3>Primary Service Areas</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>West Omaha (68118, 68130, 68154)</li>
            <li>Midtown Omaha (68131, 68132)</li>
            <li>Benson & Florence (68111, 68112)</li>
            <li>South Omaha (68107, 68108)</li>
            <li>Downtown Omaha (68102, 68105)</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="area-column">
          <h3>Extended Service Areas</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Bellevue, NE (68005, 68123)</li>
            <li>Papillion, NE (68046, 68133)</li>
            <li>La Vista, NE (68128)</li>
            <li>Gretna, NE (68028)</li>
            <li>Elkhorn, NE (68022)</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
      <p><strong>Response Times:</strong> Same-day service within 15 miles of downtown Omaha. Next-day service for extended areas.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="faq-section">
      <h2>Panel Upgrade FAQs</h2>
      <div class="faq-grid">
        <div class="faq-item">
          <h3>How much does a 200 amp panel upgrade cost in Omaha?</h3>
          <p>Panel upgrade costs typically range from $1,500 to $3,500 depending on your home's specific requirements, permit fees, and any additional electrical work needed. We provide free estimates with transparent pricing.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <h3>How long does a panel upgrade take?</h3>
          <p>Most residential panel upgrades are completed in 4-8 hours. Your power will be temporarily disconnected during installation, typically for 2-4 hours while we make the final connections.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <h3>Do I need a permit for panel upgrade in Omaha?</h3>
          <p>Yes, all electrical panel upgrades require permits from the City of Omaha. We handle all permit applications and coordinate the required inspections as part of our service.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <h3>Will upgrading my panel increase home value?</h3>
          <p>Yes, a new electrical panel can increase your home's value by $2,000-$5,000 and makes your home more attractive to buyers. It also often reduces insurance premiums.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <h3>What's the difference between 100 amp and 200 amp service?</h3>
          <p>200 amp service provides twice the electrical capacity, supporting modern appliances, HVAC systems, EV chargers, and future electrical needs without overloading circuits.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <h3>Can I add circuits during a panel upgrade?</h3>
          <p>Absolutely! Panel upgrades are the perfect time to add new circuits for hot tubs, workshops, EV chargers, or additional outlets. We can customize the installation to your needs.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="cta-section">
      <div class="cta-card">
        <h2>Ready to Upgrade Your Electrical Panel?</h2>
        <p>Don't wait for electrical problems to worsen. Get a free estimate for your panel upgrade and ensure your home's electrical system meets modern safety standards.</p>
        <div class="cta-buttons">
          <a href="/contact" class="btn-primary">Schedule Free Estimate</a>
          <a href="tel:+1-402-555-1234" class="btn-secondary">Call (402) 555-1234</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>

